South African bonds were stable on Tuesday morning having recovered after weakening substantially last week, following news that the US could hike interest rates three times in 2017.However, trade was thin with many players already on leave for the Christmas period.The local bond market is likely to take its direction from the rand this week, which was slightly firmer against most major currencies on Tuesday morning.TreasuryOne head of currency dealing Wichard Cilliers said markets were likely to remain subdued until the New Year.At 8.43am the R186 was bid at 8.980% from a previous 8.960% while the R207 was bid at 8.210%, from 8.185% previously.The bid on the US 10-year bond rate was down to 2.5662% from Monday&rsquo;s close of 2.5900%.